Files making up the server:

boot.c
	This file has the code that deals with booting PQS/8.  It sends
	the custom help loader codes and then sends the boot block.

csd.c
	This is the console serial disk server.  It includes all the
	above files.

disk.c
	This file has the code which reads and writes the virtual disk,
	floppy and DECtape images.  Upon load it validates the csd0.img
	file to verify that it is a system image and that it contains
	a valid csd boot loader and SYS handler.  If it doesn't match
	the current version the server knows it patches the boot block.

pqscsd.h
	This file is automatically derived from the latest PQS8 CSD
	handler, and contains an octal representation of the boot
	block. It is compiled in as part of disk.c.

loopback.c
	This is a test program to verify that the serial port is attached to the
	PDP-8 and working correctly.  A small program is run on the 8 to echo
	received characters back to the server.  This program can be
	found in the source code.

pdp.c
	This file has the code that sends and receives characters from
	the PDP-8.

recvtst.c
	A program to test full speed transmission of characters from the 8
	to the server.  Prints a dot for every 256 characters received.  See
	the notes at the front of the program.

tty.c
	This file has the code that displays characters on the glass Teletype
	and deals with the Unix keyboard.

textfile
	This is the file that gets sent when you press F6.  The F6 key sends
	and character and waits for it to echo.  A carriage return when sent
	expects a return and a linefeed.


Virtual disk images provided.
csd0.img
	This is the image that csd boots from.  It can be referenced
	as unit 0 from PQS/8.  It is mostly a copy of a DECtape image
	provided with the PEPS release of PQS8.

csd1.img
	This is the image mapped to unit 1;
	It is mostly a copy of another DECtape image from the
	distribution mentioned above. Up to 8 images (0-7) are
	supported.

